   "body" : "The preferences pane doesn't offer any way to specify the datadir/wallet.dat location.  This can be done with command-line flags (though this is a bit tricky on OS X), but that's awkward for the average user (and breaks when the user launches bitcoin from Spotlight or a default icon).  This would be useful for people who travel a lot (or just want security) and want to keep their wallet.dat on a keychain USB drive.\n",
